iedliche Dimensionen von Umweltgerechtigkeit machen sie diese greifbar und liefern Kontextwissen für eine längst überfällige Diskussion.  afunded by German Institute of Development and Sustainability (IDOS)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aDeutschland. 4aGeographie. 4aGesellschaft. 4aHumanökologie. 4aKlima. 4aKlimaschutz. 4aKulturgeographie. 4aNachhaltigkeit. 4aNatur. 4aPolitik. 4aSoziale Ungleichheit. 4aSozialgeographie. 4aUmweltgerechtigkeit. 4aUmweltkonflikt. 4aÖsterreich. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Human Geography.2bisacsh  aAustria.  aClimate Protection.  aClimate.  aCultural Geography.  aEnvironmental Justice.  aGeography.  aGermany.  aHuman Ecology.  aNature.  aPolitics.  aSocial Geography.  aSocial Inequality.  aSociety.  aSustainability.1 aBaasch, Stefanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBauriedl, Sybille, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeckmann, Lukas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBunge, Christiane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCavallo, Gianluca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDietl, Alena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDorndorf, Tabea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFisch, Verena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrost, Juliane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHein, Jonas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHein, Jonas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 